When I import a list of epics, they show up in the list in Portfolio using the 'epic summary' field instead of the 'epic name'. I'd prefer it used the 'epic name' as it fits more easily within the Initiatives list.

So I clicked the 'link' to the epic in JIRA and changed the summary field to be shorter and more descriptive.  Guess what?

When I save the epic and return to the Portfolio plan, the epic is now being displayed using the 'epic name'! Yay! That's what I'd like it to do but don't want to have to edit every epic to get it to show up ;)

